Cape Town - One person has been injured following a roof collapse at Somerset Mall in Somerset West this afternoon. 

  
  City of Cape Town Fire & Rescue spokesperson 
 Theo Layne said the centre was evacuated following the structural collapse. 

  

 
  "The City's Fire & Rescue Servi
  ces responded to a call out to Somerset Mall shortly after 12pm this afternoon, after a section of the roof collapsed. One person sustained injuries and was taken to hospital for treatment," Layne said.
 
 
  
 
 
  
 

 Picture: Supplied

 

 
  Somerset Mall's marketing manager Wiedaad Adams said no serious injuries were reported. "At 11:23 this morning, a portion of the ceiling in a passageway collapsed. Due to the area being cordoned off before the collapse, there were no serious injuries as a result of the incident."
 
 

 
  
   
    
   
   Picture: Supplied
  
  
 
 
  Adams said centre management and Occupational Health and Safety officials were on site to determine the cause of the incident and to assess the damage.
 
 
"The area between Entrance 1 and up until and including the Edgars court has been closed until a full assessment can be done. Clean up operations are underway," Adams said.
She said all other areas of the mall were once again fully operational.

    
   
Picture: Supplied

 
 
  
   It's the second such incident at the shopping centre in two years. Last June, the mall was evacuated after parts of the roof collapsed due to heavy rains.
  
 
 
  
 
 
